args: Hell no. Who sleeps during a festival?
I was just listening to the music\nand the chatter. ...It's nice.
Everyone's really enjoying themselves.\nI'm glad we could pull this off.
I never do a job that isn't perfect.
Maybe a bit—what with the eating and\nnapping and all. But clearly I was wrong.

You know, I bet people would trust you
more readily if you showed the same
enthusiasm you do for festivals for
other kinds of work.
Yeah, but I only wanna work\nwhen there's a festival involved.
Ha! That certainly sounds like you.\n...Say, can I ask you something?
Why did you become a festival planner?
Hm. Well. What's the dark to you?
See, to me, the dark is terror.\nIt's scary as hell.
I was abandoned in the mountains\nas a kid, and on that first night alone,\nit got dark like I never knew existed.
I figured I was gonna die all alone in that\ndark...until a festival planner saved me.
I have to admit, that's one of the more\nunusual origin stories I've ever heard.
My rescuer came from a village of festival\nplanners, so that's where I was raised.
The place was always full of happiness\nand life. It...changed me.
I found I wasn't scared of the dark if\nthere was a lantern or three around\nto light up people's faces.
There IS something special about\na festival at night.
I learned that a festival is a sorta miracle,\nand swore to bring that to everyone.
So why did you leave Hinomoto?
Figured it was only a matter of time\nbefore I was made the village leader.
And you...didn't want to do that?
Besides, Hinomoto's got loads of folks\nwho know how to put on a good festival.
But the rest of the world doesn't know\nwhat it's missing.
If there are folks who don't even know\nwhat a festival IS, it's a waste of my\ntalents not to show 'em.
Nah. I'm just living how I wanna.
Hey, aren't you the kid who told the mayor\nhe was leaving and never coming back?
Yes, but I changed my mind—and I\nwanted the two of you to know first.
I spent tonight talking to old friends and\neating snacks from my childhood and...
Well, I guess it just reminded me\nhow much I love this town.
This isn't just some place to live.\nIt's my HOME.
Sort of embarrassing how it took a\nfestival to remind me of that,\nbut there it is, I guess.
I mean, what good is a home if the people\nwho live there don't protect it?
Damn straight—although you've also\ngot this prince here to help you out.
That's right. If you're ever in danger,\nyou can always count on us.
I hope I never have to take you up on that.\nAnyway, my friends are waiting, so...
Seems like the mayor has\nnothing to worry about.
'Course they are! Why else would a lazy\nidiot like me spend so much time on 'em?
I wonder if you'd be willing to put a little\nsomething together for the castle?
We have a lot of refugees there,\nmany who have suffered great loss.
I think you'd be just the person to\nlighten their hearts a little bit.
Okay, but you'll have to pay me—\nand don't say I owe you because\nof all the meals you bought!
Heh. I'm happy to pay you, Yaten.
Hell, if I stick with you, I'll probably run\ninto all kinds of folks who need the power\nof a festival to lift their spirits.
And whenever I take a job,\nI always deliver the best!
